original.description: Full precision FP32 model with external data file

quantized.description: Quantized INT8 model optimized for web inference

generator.description: TinyDiT generator model for cat image synthesis with breed conditioning

inputs.name: noise
inputs.description: Gaussian noise tensor for generation start point

output.name: velocity
output.description: Predicted velocity for flow matching ODE integration

sampling.description: Run model iteratively from t=0 to t=1, updating: x(t+dt) = x(t) + dt * velocity

recommendation_reason: The quantized classifier is 4x smaller (11 MB vs 43 MB) and provides faster inference. The generator model uses CFG scale 1.5 for better sample quality.

breed_classes.note: This is a binary cat vs other classifier. For breed-specific classification, the model outputs 2 classes:

classes.name: cat
classes.description: Image contains a cat (any of 12 breeds: Abyssinian, Bengal, Birman, Bombay, British Shorthair, Egyptian Mau, Maine Coon, Persian, Ragdoll, Russian Blue, Siamese, Sphynx)

classes.name: other
classes.description: Image contains a non-cat (primarily dogs used as negative samples)

generator_breeds.note: Generator supports 13 breed classes for conditional image generation
